1 g. The number of actively missing indigenous people by year;
2 h. A description of the activities and progress related to improving interagency
3 communication, cooperation, and collaboration and removing interjurisdictional
4 barriers; and
5 i. Any other information the task force finds relevant to the task force's mission.
6 6. The task force may make recommendations to federal, state, and local agencies in
7 carrying out the task force's duties.
8 7. Money in the missing indigenous people grant fund is appropriated on a continuing
9 basis to the task force for the purpose of supporting the efforts of a federally
10 recognized Indian nation, tribe, or band in this state, to identify, report, and find
11 missing indigenous people. The director of the office of management and budget shall
12 transfer any funds remaining in the missing indigenous people grant fund after July 31,
13 2035, to the general fund.
14 8. The attorney general shall implement a missing person repository for authorized users
15 to enter missing person information in accordance with rules established by the
16 bureau of criminal investigation. Missing person information, including demographic
17 data related to indigenous people, which is entered by an authorized user or made
18 available to an authorized user by a federally recognized tribe in this state must be
19 included in the repository. Records under this subsection are exempt records that may
20 be disclosed only in accordance with bureau of criminal investigation rules.
21 SECTION 3. APPROPRIATION - TRANSFER - MISSING INDIGENOUS PEOPLE GRANT
22 PROGRAM FUND. There is appropriated out of any moneys in the general fund in the state
23 treasury, not otherwise appropriated, the sum of $250,000, or so much of the sum as may be
24 necessary, which the office of management and budget shall transfer to the missing indigenous
25 people grant fund for the purpose of supporting the efforts of a federally recognized Indian
26 nation, tribe, or band in this state, to identify, report, and find missing indigenous people, for the
27 biennium beginning July 1, 2025, and ending June 30, 2027.
28 SECTION 4. EXPIRATION DATE. Sections 1 and 2 of this Act are effective through July 31,
29 2035, and after that date are ineffective.
